s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2533:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png" alt="logo-512x512" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-699" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-300x300.png 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-150x150.png 150w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-200x200.png 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-450x450.png 450w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-90x90.png 90w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png 512w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>A bunch of tweaks and improvements including sortable columns in the dashboard. The dynamic mode can now be turned off for mobile devices. In recent versions it was disabled without an option. This is of-course to maintain a working advert on smaller devices if you don&#8217;t use mobile adverts. Not every theme handles the fixed size very well. Depending on your theme this option then makes sense or not. Also the exporting of adverts didn&#8217;t always work. This has been fixed.</p>\n<h2>Changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[new] Option to disable dynamic mode on mobile devices</li>\n<li>[new] Basic sortable columns for most dashboard tables</li>\n<li>[fix] Exporting adverts not always working for some users</li>\n<li>[change] Responsive feature is now deprecated</li>\n<li>[i18n] Updated translation files</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>When not doing internet things</h2>\n<p>A little while ago I stumbled on a bunch of fishermen who were a few hands short reeling in their net. So I helped them pull the thing onto the beach. It was loaded with fish.</p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing.jpg" rel="lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9056" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing-300x225.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"Omnikassa for WooCommerce 1.3.3 – Updated";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://ajdg.solutions/2015/11/24/omnikassa-for-woocommerce-1-3-3-updated/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 04:05:23 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:23:"Payment Gateway Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"woocommerce";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"improvements