0w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/wc-omnicard-logo.jpg 380w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>A small maintenance update fixing the dashboard links in the plugin to more relevant items. Also the Dutch translation has been updated. Some typos removed.</p>\n<h2>Changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[change] Updated credits links</li>\n<li>[i18n] Updated Dutch translation</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Automatic updates</h2>\n<p>OmniKassa (OmniCard) for WooCommerce has automatic updates. This was introduced earlier this year in version 1.3.2. If you have this version already the update will show in your websites dashboard. With a valid license you can update the plugin automatically just like other plugins.</p>\n<h3>Manual update steps:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Download the latest version from your <a href="https://ajdg.solutions/my-account/">account</a> on this website.</li>\n<li>Unzip the ‘omnicard.zip’ file.</li>\n<li>Log in to your website files with your favorite (s)FTP account.</li>\n<li>Browse to the ‘/wp-content/plugins/’ folder.</li>\n<li>Upload the unzipped ‘omnicard’ folder to the ‘wp-content/plugins/’ folder and overwrite the current folder.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Because this update is rather small/minor, you do not have to disable the plugin while updating. For other updates disabling the plugin before updating is advised.</em></p>\n<p>If you need help updating the plugin I can install the update for a small fee.<br />\nPlease select the Installation service from the <a href="https://ajdg.solutions/products/omnikassa-for-woocommerce/">Omnikassa product page</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6