\n<p>We will be keeping new support ticket creation open until the end of this week (including the weekend) and closing new ticket creation on Monday the 21st (9am UK time).</p>\n<p>This will allow us to answer already created tickets between Monday (21st) and Wednesday (23rd) before we stop on Christmas Eve (24th) for a few days.</p>\n<p>New ticket creation will then re-open on the 28th until the 30th (9am UK time). We will then be closed for another few days to bring in the new year. Normal support services will resume from Monday the 4th of January.</p>\n<p>We will be using the holidays to catch up with family and friends and recharge the batteries before starting what will be a very busy 2016 with many greats improvements coming to Ultimate Member.</p>\n<p>We wish you a Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year and look forward to helping you continue to build greats things with Ultimate Member in 2016!</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Christmas &amp; New Year Support Schedule:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Thursday 17th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Friday 18th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Saturday 19th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Sunday 20th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Monday 21st Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Tuesday 22nd Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Wednesday 23rd Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <strong><span style="color: #62d85f;">YES</span></strong></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Thursday 24th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Friday 25th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <strong><span style="color: #ef6060;">NO</span></strong> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Saturday 26th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <strong><span style="color: #ef6060;">NO</span></strong> &#8211; Support Team Working: <strong><span style="color: #ef6060;">NO</span></strong></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Sunday 27th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <strong><span style="color: #ef6060;">NO</span></strong> &#8211; Support Team Working: <strong><span style="color: #ef6060;">NO</span></strong></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Monday 28th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <strong><span style="color: #62d85f;">YES</span></strong> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Tuesday 29th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Wednesday 30th Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #62d85f;"><strong>YES</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Thursday 31st Dec &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Friday 1st Jan &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Saturday 2nd Jan &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Sunday 3rd Jan &#8211; New Ticket Creation: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span> &#8211; Support Team Working: <span style="color: #ef6060;"><strong>NO</strong></span></li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Monday 4th Jan &#8211; Normal support resumes</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com/support-over-the-holidays/">Support over the holidays</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com">Ultimate Member</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"https://ultimatemember.com/support-over-the-holidays/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"3";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"Lessons learned from running a freemium WordPress plugin business";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"https://ultimatemember.com/lessons-learned-running-fremium-wordpress-plugin-business/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"https://ultimatemember.com/lessons-learned-running-fremium-wordpress-plugin-business/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 06 Dec 2015 01:33:45 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"https://ultimatemember.com/?p=117459";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:528:"<p>Last week our free WordPress plugin Ultimate Member passed the 20,00 active install mark, so I thought I&#8217;d share some of the things we have learnt and the challenges we have faced since we launched the plugin 10 months ago....</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com/lessons-learned-running-fremium-wordpress-plugin-business/">Lessons learned from running a freemium WordPress plugin business</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com">Ultimate Member</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Calum Allison";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7396:"<p>Last week our free WordPress plugin <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/ultimate-member/">Ultimate Member</a> passed the 20,00 active install mark, so I thought I&#8217;d share some of the things we have learnt and the challenges we have faced since we launched the plugin 10 months ago.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Plugin Support</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Prior to launching Ultimate Member we made the decision that we would provide support to all users of the plugin, regardless of whether they were a free user or a paying customer. We made this decision to increase our conversion rate and reduce the likelihood of receiving 1 star reviews for lack of support which are so often seen in the plugin repo.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Whilst we believe this has been the right decision for us and helped us to quickly grow our revenue to over $20,000 a month it is not without its challenges.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">For example, with a conversion rate of around 8.5% for Ultimate Member this means over 90% of the users of our plugin have not paid for any of our extensions. Assuming every active install of the plugin is a different user that means we are providing support to a free user base of over 18,000 people.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">That&#8217;s a huge number of people to provide support for and the amount of time we spend on support would be greatly reduced were we to only provide support to paying customers.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Forum vs Email Ticketing </span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">When we launched the plugin we decided to provide support via a forum using <a href="https://bbpress.org/">bbPress</a>. Our thought process for using a forum was users would help other users out and people could find the answers to questions already answered so they would not need to create new topics. This would help to reduce the support burden and allow us to spend more time developing the plugin.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Unfortunately that was not the case and as our user base grew and the amount of topics being created each month increased it became harder and harder to provide support via the forum. Whilst we did have a few users who would be active on the forums and help other users out, the vast majority of the tickets were answered by us.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">So for us the benefit of users helping on the forum was massively outweighed by the negatives that came with managing support via a forum. The main pain points for us were: multiple topics would be created for already answered topics; users posting issues on topics not related to their issue and not being able to track or assign topics.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">We decided a couple of months ago to switch to an email ticketing system using <a href="http://www.helpscout.net/">HelpScout</a>. Our decision to close the support forum and move to HelpScout whilst not universally popular with all of our users, has been the right decision.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">It is now much easier for us to manage support as we can track open tickets, assign tickets to the right person and deliver better one-to-one support.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">So if you are about to launch a new plugin/theme and are not sure on which method to use for support, I highly recommend opting for a dedicated helpdesk solution such as HelpScout over a forum based approach.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">High Growth </span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Ultimate Member has grown from 0 to 20,000 active installs in the 10 months since we launched the plugin. Whilst we are extremely happy that Ultimate Member has been so popular and is a now a viable full-time business with decent revenue, experiencing high growth is not without its challenges.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The main challenge we have experienced is the sheer quantity of support tickets created by users of the plugin. For example last month alone, we dealt with over 800 tickets not including the near 200 topics created on the WP forum over the last two months.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The increase in demand for support has been very difficult to manage between the two of us over the last few months which is why we made the decision recently to expand the team and bring someone in to help with support.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-117489" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hsnovemeber.png" alt="hsnovemeber" width="1000" height="353" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hsnovemeber-300x106.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hsnovemeber.png 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Hiring Staff  </span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The single biggest mistake we have made since we launched the plugin is not hiring soon enough. By not hiring someone sooner it has negatively effected the business in several ways:</p>\n<ol>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Support response/resolution times have been slower</li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Taken time away from other important parts of the business e.g marketing, documentation writing</li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Decreased productivity due to burnout</li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Slowed down development of plugin &amp; extensions</li>\n<li style="text-align: left;">Resulted in a drop in revenue</li>\n</ol>\n<p>So in addition to effecting our revenue it has also resulted in users becoming worried about the long-term future of the plugin when they see development slow, no new blog posts and slower response times to support.</p>\n<p>Whilst we did not hire soon enough, after witnessing the impacts on our business of being over-stretched we focused on growing the team and bringing someone in to help get us back on track for the future.</p>\n<p>If you run a WordPress plugin/theme business I would recommend hiring someone to help with support as soon as your revenue levels allow for it. It will result in a better product, happier customers and a greater work-life balance for yourself.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Moving forward  </span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The last few months have been very demanding but we are hopeful the changes we have made in moving support to HelpScout and hiring staff will enable us to take Ultimate Member to the next level which will see more improvements to the core plugin/existing extensions, faster development of new extensions and improved support.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The will hopefully allow us to increase the user base of the plugin, grow revenue and expand the team further to ensure a proper work-life balance and happy customers.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com/lessons-learned-running-fremium-wordpress-plugin-business/">Lessons learned from running a freemium WordPress plugin business</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com">Ultimate Member</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:90:"https://ultimatemember.com/lessons-learned-running-fremium-wordpress-plugin-business/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"12";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"Inside Ultimate Member: July 2015";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"https://ultimatemember.com/inside-ultimate-member-july-2015/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"https://ultimatemember.com/inside-ultimate-member-july-2015/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 24 Aug 2015 05:50:01 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"https://ultimatemember.com/?p=69253";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:471:"<p>Dealing with a hangover from a price increase and experiencing our first month where revenue has not grown. Here is how we got on during July. E-commerce Metrics Our total revenue for the month of June was $22,405 which is a 9%...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com/inside-ultimate-member-july-2015/">Inside Ultimate Member: July 2015</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com">Ultimate Member</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Calum Allison";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7568:"<p>Dealing with a hangover from a price increase and experiencing our first month where revenue has not grown. Here is how we got on during July.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">E-commerce Metrics</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Our total revenue for the month of June was $22,405 which is a 9% decrease from May where revenue was $24,628.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The revenue was generated from 256 orders and we have been able to increase our average spend per customer to $98. This is an increase of $3 from June when it was $95.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The average daily revenue for the month was $723. A decrease of $98 from June.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">If you want to see more of our metrics you can view them in real-time via our <a href="https://ultimatemember.com/open-metrics/">open metics dashboard</a>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-69257 size-full" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/revenuedash.png" alt="" width="1680" height="1196" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/revenuedash-300x214.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/revenuedash-1024x729.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1680px) 100vw, 1680px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Active installs</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Our plugin page shows our active install count as 10,000+. This is the same as June and is due to the way the WordPress directory displays installs. Once a plugin reaches 10,000+ installs the install range they use increases in blocks of 10,000.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Because of this, we will no longer be able to gauge accurately our monthly active installs.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">The effects of a price increase</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">This month was the first month we have not released any new extensions. This was due in part to focusing on improvements/issues to existing extensions and the core plugin and also an increase in the amount of time we have had to spend on support.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Since it has been a quiet month for extensions, I have decided to discuss the results we found from increasing the price of our most popular product &#8211; the <a href="https://ultimatemember.com/core-extensions-bundle/">core extensions bundle</a>.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">It started on the 11th of June when we announced that the price of the bundle would be increasing by $50 to $199 via an email campaign and blog post.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">As you can see from the chart below (bundle sales during June &amp; July), sales of the bundle went up after the announcment, with very high sales on the deadline day and the day after (we gave late stragglers a grace period for getting the bundle after the &#8220;deadline&#8221;).</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">However, you can also see from the chart that the first half of July sales of bundle were quite low. This was in part due to customers rushing to buy the bundle prior to the price increase and also due to the higher price of the bundle possibly putting potential customers off or not being perceived as offering enough value/savings to justify the purchase.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-69263" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/junejulybundlesales-1024x292.png" alt="junejulybundlesales" width="980" height="279" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/junejulybundlesales-300x86.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/junejulybundlesales-1024x292.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Free Support</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">This month we&#8217;ve had 503 new topics created on our forum. That&#8217;s an average of 16.2 new topics created each day and is only 1 less topic than was created in June. This brings the total number of topics created on our forum to 3123.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Mailing List</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">At the end of July our mailing list stood at 6,610 people with 1526 people subscribing to our list in July. The rate at which people have been added to mailing list has been very steady the last few months with around 1,400 to 1,600 joining each month.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Since nearly all of our subsribers opt-in via our built in plugin notice it suggests our plugin user adopotion rate is not growing significantly from around 2,000 active installs a month.<a href="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-05-31-at-21.48.24.png"><br />\n</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-69270" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/mailchimp.png" alt="mailchimp" width="896" height="564" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/mailchimp-300x189.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/mailchimp.png 896w" sizes="(max-width: 896px) 100vw, 896px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Website traffic</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">This month we&#8217;ve had 33,701 sessions and 15,721 users on the site which resulted in 161,585 page views. These figures represent a growth of 5.63% for sessions,  3.63% for users and 3.2% for page views on the previous month.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-76587" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ga1-1024x245.png" alt="ga1" width="980" height="234" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ga1-300x72.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ga1-1024x245.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">A breakdown of our traffic sources with Google, Direct and WordPress.org bringing in the most news users.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-76588" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ga2-1024x482.png" alt="ga2" width="980" height="461" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ga2-300x141.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ga2-1024x482.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Summary</span></p>\n<p>Overall, July has been a solid month for us but it was always going to be difficult in terms of increasing revenue after having so many customers panic buy in June to take advantage of the cheaper bundle price.</p>\n<p>It also shows the importance of continuing to keep working on building new extensions and increasing the perceived value of the bundle. Thankfully, we will soon be releasing our activity extension which we think will be very popular and help to grow revenue and increase bundle sales.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com/inside-ultimate-member-july-2015/">Inside Ultimate Member: July 2015</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com">Ultimate Member</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://ultimatemember.com/inside-ultimate-member-july-2015/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"Introducing Social Activity Extension";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://ultimatemember.com/introducing-social-activity-extension/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://ultimatemember.com/introducing-social-activity-extension/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 14 Aug 2015 07:38:37 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"https://ultimatemember.com/?p=71297";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:461:"<p>We are very excited to introduce you to our latest extension and let you know what it can do and what improvements we will be making to the extension after the initial release. Also if you go to bottom of post...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com/introducing-social-activity-extension/">Introducing Social Activity Extension</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com">Ultimate Member</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Calum Allison";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7935:"<p>We are very excited to introduce you to our latest extension and let you know what it can do and what improvements we will be making to the extension after the initial release. Also if you go to bottom of post you will also see we are running a giveway where you can win a free license for this extension.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">User Wall</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The extension adds a new tab to user profiles which will allow a user to see all of their posts, posts they have received from other users and allow them to create new posts.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71452" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/activity-1.png" alt="activity (1)" width="800" height="574" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/activity-1-300x215.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/activity-1.png 800w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Activity Feed</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The extension creates a new page called activity and this is where a user can see all posts created on the site from all users.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Photos</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The posting interface allows users to upload and attach a photo to a post. The user can upload a photo and also write custom text above photo. Only one photo can be uploaded per post.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71443" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.06.47.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015-08-14 at 21.06.47" width="700" height="721" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.06.47-291x300.png 291w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.06.47.png 700w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">YouTube/Vimeo</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">If a user pastes a Youtube or Vimeo link into a post it will automatically be embedded into the post so users can watch the video without leaving the site. Note: The post will only embed the first url added. If a user adds any more links to a post they will appear as links only.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71445" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.07.18.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015-08-14 at 21.07.18" width="700" height="659" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.07.18-300x282.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.07.18.png 700w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Likes</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The extension allows users to like a post. If a post is liked it will instantly increase the like counter. The posting interface will show the profile images of some of the people who have liked the post and a user can see a full list of who has liked a post by clicking on one of the profile pics, which will open up the like modal.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Comments</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The extension allows users to comment on a user&#8217;s post. It is also possible to like comments and also reply to individual comments. To keep the activity feed clean the plugin by default will only show two comments with the rest only appearing when &#8220;load more comments&#8221; is clicked. As an admin you can set in options how many comments to show initially and how many to load when a user click &#8220;load more comments&#8221;.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71446" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.15.37.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015-08-14 at 21.15.37" width="700" height="451" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.15.37-300x193.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.15.37.png 700w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;"># Hashtags</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The extension allows users to add hashtags to their posts. Users can then click on the hashtag to view all activity posts which contain that hashtag.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71444" src="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.07.03.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015-08-14 at 21.07.03" width="700" height="270" srcset="https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.07.03-300x116.png 300w, https://ultimatemember.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-14-at-21.07.03.png 700w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Role Settings</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The extension allows you to set different permissions for each user role. You can make it so the activity tab only shows on certain user profiles; prevent a user role from creating posts; prevent users from being able to attach a photo to a post and prevent a user role from commenting on posts.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Performance</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">To make the extension as efficient and quick as possible we have added in lazy load for posts. By default the extension will load 10 posts at a time and will load more as user scrolls down page. As admin you can set in options how many posts you want to be loaded at a time and you can set a different number for mobile devices.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">What&#8217;s coming in future updates?</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">We believe in the MVP approach to products and getting early feedback from users. The initial release of the extension has mainly focused on the posting interface. Much more is planned with this extension including showing activity on the feed which shows other interactions on site e.g John Doe created a new blog post etc.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">Giveway</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">In conjuction with the upcoming release of the extension, we are running another giveway where we are giving away 5 annual licenses for the extension. So if you&#8217;d like to be in with a chance of winning one of the free licenses then just enter the giveway below. The more actions you complete the higher chance you will have of winning <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f609.png" alt="😉" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> The giveway will end on Monday.</p>\n<p><a id="rcwidget_pv5pgb85" class="rcptr" href="http://www.rafflecopter.com/rafl/display/fbeae2a02/" rel="nofollow" data-raflid="fbeae2a02" data-theme="classic" data-template="">a Rafflecopter giveaway</a><br />\n<script src="//widget-prime.rafflecopter.com/launch.js"></script></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com/introducing-social-activity-extension/">Introducing Social Activity Extension</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ultimatemember.com">Ultimate Member</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://ultimatemember.com/introducing-social-activity-extension/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"17";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"Win a free one year core extensions bundle license";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"https://ultimatemember.com/win-free-one-year-core-extensions-bundle-license/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xm